let the cat out of the bag.data-term: let the cat out of the bag

examples.en: He kept blabbing on and on about politics.
Don't tell Mary. She'll blab it all over town.
Don't go blabbing to your friends about this.
Don't tell Mary our secret, she's sure to blab it out.
...a trustworthy bodyguard who would never blab to the tabloids...
How did she find out about the surprise party? Tom blabbed.
